sentences: Stella Donnelly (born 10 April 1992) is a Welsh-Australian musician.
Born in Western Australia to a Welsh mother, she spent some childhood years living in Morriston before moving to Perth, Australia with her family.
Donnelly first started singing when she joined a rock band in high school (Irene McCormack Catholic College) that performed Green Day covers.

sentences: Her 2017 debut single "Boys Will be Boys", written about societal attitudes towards women and her friend's experience of sexual assault, was dubbed a "#MeToo anthem" (despite being written and released prior to the widespread global coverage of the movement).

sentences: Donnelly is opposed to the celebration of Australia Day.
